{"title":"Cèlia Estruch-Garcia","markdown":{"yaml":{"title":"Cèlia Estruch-Garcia","description-meta":"Academic Website Cèlia Estruch-Garcia","image":"profile_photo_lse_cut.png","page-navigation":false,"toc":false,"page-layout":"full","format":{"html":{"css":"styles.css"}}},"headingText":"Research","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n<div style=\"display: flex; align-items: flex-start; justify-content: center; gap: 3rem; flex-wrap: wrap;\">\n\n\n<!-- LEFT COLUMN -->\n<div style=\"flex: 0 0 280px; text-align: left; margin-right: 2rem;\">\n\n<img src=\"profile_photo_lse_cut.png\" alt=\"Cèlia Estruch Garcia\" style=\"width: 100%; border-radius: 8px;\">\n\n\n<p><strong>Cèlia Estruch Garcia</strong><br>\nPhD Researcher, Department of Government<br>\n<a href=\"https://www.lse.ac.uk/government/\" target=\"_blank\">London School of Economics</a>\ncestruch@alumni.lse.ac.uk</p>\n\n<div style=\"display: flex; gap: 24px; margin-top: 1rem;\">\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/cestruchg\" target=\"_blank\">\n    <img src=\"icons/icon_github.png\" alt=\"GitHub\" style=\"height: 24px; margin-right: 4px\">\n  </a>\n  <a href=\"https://linkedin.com/in/celia-estruch/\" target=\"_blank\">\n    <img src=\"icons/icon_linkedin.png\" alt=\"LinkedIn\" style=\"height: 33px; margin-right: 2px\">\n  </a>\n  <a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=tertKG4AAAAJ&hl=ca\" target=\"_blank\">\n    <img src=\"icons/icon_scholar.png\" alt=\"Scholar\" style=\"height: 24px; margin-right: 8px\">\n  </a>\n  <a href=\"https://bsky.app/profile/celiaestruch.bsky.social\" target=\"_blank\">\n    <img src=\"icons/icon_bluesky.png\" alt=\"Bluesky\" style=\"height: 24px; margin-right: 8px\">\n  </a>\n  <a href=\"https://x.com/celiaestruch\" target=\"_blank\">\n    <img src=\"icons/icon_x.png\" alt=\"X\" style=\"height: 24px;\">\n  </a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n</div>\n\n\n<!-- RIGHT COLUMN -->\n<div style=\"flex: 1.5; min-width: 400px; text-align: justify;\">\n\nWelcome! I am an incoming Doctoral Researcher at the Department of Government at the <a href=\"https://www.lse.ac.uk/government/\" target=\"_blank\">London School of Economics and Political Science (LSE)</a>. My research focuses on the distributive and political impacts of sustainable urban policies.\n\nBefore starting my PhD, I worked as a Research Assistant at <a href=\"https://ieb.ub.edu/en/\" target=\"_blank\">Barcelona's Institute of Economics (IEB)</a> and the <a href=\"https://www.uoc.edu/en\" target=\"_blank\">Open University of Catalonia (UOC)</a>.\n\nI hold a <a href=\"https://www.lse.ac.uk/study-at-lse/graduate/msc-political-science-political-science-and-political-economy\" target=\"_blank\">Master's degree in Political Science and Political Economy</a> from LSE, a <a href=\"https://www.upf.edu/en/web/graus/grau-filosofia-politica-economia\" target=\"_blank\">Bachelor's in Philosophy, Politics and Economics</a> from Pompeu Fabra University, and training in <a href=\"https://web.ub.edu/en/web/estudis/w/specificmasterdegree-202311953\" target=\"_blank\">Data Analysis for Social Sciences</a> from the University of Barcelona.\n\n---\n\n\n#### Submitted for Publication\n\n**The electoral effects of banning cars from the streets: Evidence from Barcelona’s Superblocks**  \n_with [Albert Solé-Ollé](https://albertsoleolle.wordpress.com/), [Filippo Tassinari](https://sites.google.com/view/filippotassinari/home-page), and [Elisabet Viladecans-Marsal](https://elisabetviladecansmarsal.com/)._  [CEPR DP19915](https://hub.cepr.org/civicrm/file?id=227076&eid=235822&fcs=1c09bbc55709d2bc0317dcd9e2fe39cc78bcf000513f08d26acbc6d17cd37b2d_1745310367_168)  \n- Awards: Best Paper Award at the [11th Environmental Politics and Governance Conference](https://www.epg2025.org/).  \n- Media: [VoxTalks Economics](https://cepr.org/multimedia/do-car-bans-hurt-politicians)\n\n\n**Do climate events drive support for climate change policies?**  \n_with [Toni Rodon](https://tonirodon.cat/), [Marc Guinjoan](https://sites.google.com/site/engmarcguinjoan?authuser=0), and [Roger Sanjaume](https://rogersanjaume.cat/)._ [Abstract](https://www.ub.edu/portal/web/dp-cpdcfd/novetats/-/detall/-do-climate-events-drive-support-for-climate-change-policies-toni-rodon-upf-marc-guinjoan-uab-)\n\n#### Work in Progress\n\n**Taking out the Trash: Political implications of door-to-door waste management in Catalonia**  \n_with [Max Bradley](https://www.eui.eu/people?id=max-bradley) and [Pau Grau-Vilalta](https://paugrau.cat/)._\n\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":"\n\n<div style=\"display: flex; align-items: flex-start; justify-content: center; gap: 3rem; flex-wrap: wrap;\">\n\n\n<!-- LEFT COLUMN -->\n<div style=\"flex: 0 0 280px; text-align: left; margin-right: 2rem;\">\n\n<img src=\"profile_photo_lse_cut.png\" alt=\"Cèlia Estruch Garcia\" style=\"width: 100%; border-radius: 8px;\">\n\n\n<p><strong>Cèlia Estruch Garcia</strong><br>\nPhD Researcher, Department of Government<br>\n<a href=\"https://www.lse.ac.uk/government/\" target=\"_blank\">London School of Economics</a>\ncestruch@alumni.lse.ac.uk</p>\n\n<div style=\"display: flex; gap: 24px; margin-top: 1rem;\">\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/cestruchg\" target=\"_blank\">\n    <img src=\"icons/icon_github.png\" alt=\"GitHub\" style=\"height: 24px; margin-right: 4px\">\n  </a>\n  <a href=\"https://linkedin.com/in/celia-estruch/\" target=\"_blank\">\n    <img src=\"icons/icon_linkedin.png\" alt=\"LinkedIn\" style=\"height: 33px; margin-right: 2px\">\n  </a>\n  <a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=tertKG4AAAAJ&hl=ca\" target=\"_blank\">\n    <img src=\"icons/icon_scholar.png\" alt=\"Scholar\" style=\"height: 24px; margin-right: 8px\">\n  </a>\n  <a href=\"https://bsky.app/profile/celiaestruch.bsky.social\" target=\"_blank\">\n    <img src=\"icons/icon_bluesky.png\" alt=\"Bluesky\" style=\"height: 24px; margin-right: 8px\">\n  </a>\n  <a href=\"https://x.com/celiaestruch\" target=\"_blank\">\n    <img src=\"icons/icon_x.png\" alt=\"X\" style=\"height: 24px;\">\n  </a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n</div>\n\n\n<!-- RIGHT COLUMN -->\n<div style=\"flex: 1.5; min-width: 400px; text-align: justify;\">\n\nWelcome! I am an incoming Doctoral Researcher at the Department of Government at the <a href=\"https://www.lse.ac.uk/government/\" target=\"_blank\">London School of Economics and Political Science (LSE)</a>. My research focuses on the distributive and political impacts of sustainable urban policies.\n\nBefore starting my PhD, I worked as a Research Assistant at <a href=\"https://ieb.ub.edu/en/\" target=\"_blank\">Barcelona's Institute of Economics (IEB)</a> and the <a href=\"https://www.uoc.edu/en\" target=\"_blank\">Open University of Catalonia (UOC)</a>.\n\nI hold a <a href=\"https://www.lse.ac.uk/study-at-lse/graduate/msc-political-science-political-science-and-political-economy\" target=\"_blank\">Master's degree in Political Science and Political Economy</a> from LSE, a <a href=\"https://www.upf.edu/en/web/graus/grau-filosofia-politica-economia\" target=\"_blank\">Bachelor's in Philosophy, Politics and Economics</a> from Pompeu Fabra University, and training in <a href=\"https://web.ub.edu/en/web/estudis/w/specificmasterdegree-202311953\" target=\"_blank\">Data Analysis for Social Sciences</a> from the University of Barcelona.\n\n---\n\n### Research\n\n#### Submitted for Publication\n\n**The electoral effects of banning cars from the streets: Evidence from Barcelona’s Superblocks**  \n_with [Albert Solé-Ollé](https://albertsoleolle.wordpress.com/), [Filippo Tassinari](https://sites.google.com/view/filippotassinari/home-page), and [Elisabet Viladecans-Marsal](https://elisabetviladecansmarsal.com/)._  [CEPR DP19915](https://hub.cepr.org/civicrm/file?id=227076&eid=235822&fcs=1c09bbc55709d2bc0317dcd9e2fe39cc78bcf000513f08d26acbc6d17cd37b2d_1745310367_168)  \n- Awards: Best Paper Award at the [11th Environmental Politics and Governance Conference](https://www.epg2025.org/).  \n- Media: [VoxTalks Economics](https://cepr.org/multimedia/do-car-bans-hurt-politicians)\n\n\n**Do climate events drive support for climate change policies?**  \n_with [Toni Rodon](https://tonirodon.cat/), [Marc Guinjoan](https://sites.google.com/site/engmarcguinjoan?authuser=0), and [Roger Sanjaume](https://rogersanjaume.cat/)._ [Abstract](https://www.ub.edu/portal/web/dp-cpdcfd/novetats/-/detall/-do-climate-events-drive-support-for-climate-change-policies-toni-rodon-upf-marc-guinjoan-uab-)\n\n#### Work in Progress\n\n**Taking out the Trash: Political implications of door-to-door waste management in Catalonia**  \n_with [Max Bradley](https://www.eui.eu/people?id=max-bradley) and [Pau Grau-Vilalta](https://paugrau.cat/)._\n\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n"},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"markdown"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":"none","code-overflow":"scroll","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":false,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"latex-clean":true,"latex-min-runs":1,"latex-max-runs":10,"latex-makeindex":"makeindex","latex-makeindex-opts":[],"latex-tlmgr-opts":[],"latex-input-paths":[],"latex-output-dir":null,"link-external-icon":false,"link-external-newwindow":false,"self-contained-math":false,"format-resources":[],"notebook-links":true},"pandoc":{"standalone":